PFD: 25-Jun-25
HB7 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to crimes and offenses; to amend Sections
4 13A-10-240, 13A-10-241, 13A-10-242, and 16-1-24.1, Code of
5 Alabama 1975; to provide for the definition of a "credible
6 threat"; to revise the elements of and provide further for the
7 penalties for the crime of making a terrorist threat in the
8 first and second degrees; to require a public school principal
9 to immediately notify law enforcement if the conduct of the
10 student warrants the charge of making a terrorist threat in
11 the first or second degree; to specifically provide that being
12 charged with either crime is a reason for which a student
13 shall immediately be suspended for a minimum of one year; to
14 provide further for the conditions of readmittance; to provide
15 for restitution upon a finding of guilt; and to add Section
16 13A-10-243 to the Code of Alabama 1975; to require any person
17 found guilty of making a terrorist threat in the first or
18 second degree to make restitution.
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
20 Section 1. Sections 13A-10-240, 13A-10-241, 13A-10-242,
21 and 16-1-24.1 of the Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read
22 as follows:
23 "§13A-10-240
24 As used in this article, the following terms have the
25 following meanings:
26 (1) CREDIBLE THREAT. A knowing and willful statement or
27 course of conduct which, based on the totality of the
28 circumstances, would cause a reasonable person to fear for his
