29 or her safety or the safety of another.
30 (2) GOVERNMENT. The term as defined in Section
31 13A-10-1.
32 (3) GOVERNMENTAL FUNCTION. The term as defined in
33 Section 13A-10-1.
34 (1)(4) PROPERTY. Personal or real property. The term
35 includes, but is not limited to, any of the following
36 buildings or real property:
37 a. A church, mosque, synagogue, or other religious real
38 property.
39 b. A public or private school.
40 c. A hospital, nursing home, or other building housing
41 disabled or immobile individuals.
42 (2) THREATEN. A person threatens another if all of the
43 following occur:
44 a. The person intentionally and knowingly makes a
45 statement verbally, in writing, by means of an electronic
46 communication device, or by any other means to harm a person
47 or property.
48 b. The statement is communicated to another person.
49 c. Under the circumstances, the threatened harm is
50 credible and imminent.
51 d. The statement, on its face and under the
52 circumstances in which it is made, is so unequivocal,
53 immediate, and specific as to convey to the person threatened,
54 a gravity of purpose and an immediate prospect of execution of
55 the threat.
56 e. The statement causes the person to reasonably be in
