124 "§16-1-24.1
125 (a) The Legislature finds a compelling public interest
126 in ensuring that schools are made safe and drug-free for all
127 students and school employees. The Legislature finds the need
128 for a comprehensive safe school and drug-free school policy to
129 be adopted by the State Board of Education. This policy should
130 establish minimum standards for classes of offenses and
131 prescribe uniform minimum procedures and penalties for those
132 who violate the policies. It is the intent of the Legislature
133 that our schools remain safe and drug-free for all students
134 and school employees. The State Board of Education shall adopt
135 and all local boards of education shall uniformly enforce
136 policies that protect all students and school employees. The
137 State Board of Education shall require local school systems to
138 modify their policies, practices, or procedures so as to
139 ensure a safe school environment free of illegal drugs,
140 alcohol, or weapons. Any rules and regulations adopted by the
