322 Section 2. Section 13A-10-243 is added to the Code of
323 Alabama 1975, to read as follows:
324 §13A-10-243
325 (a) A person convicted or adjudicated of making a
326 terrorist threat in the first degree or second degree shall be
327 ordered to make restitution as follows:
328 (1) To the owner of any real property or school,
329 church, or governmental entity affected by the making of the
330 terrorist threat.
331 (2) To the primary investigative law enforcement and
332 prosecutorial entities for any legitimate cost incurred in the
333 course of the investigation or prosecution. Where the
334 terrorist threat results in an emergency response, the
335 defendant shall be ordered to pay restitution for the expenses
336 incurred by any local, state, or federal law enforcement or
Page 12

incurred by any local, state, or federal law enforcement or
HB7 Enrolled
337 assisting governmental agency. Expenses include any reasonable
338 costs directly incurred, including the costs of police,
339 firefighting, and emergency medical services, and the
340 personnel costs of those persons who respond to the incident.
341 (b) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the
342 total amount of restitution ordered pursuant to this section
343 shall not exceed ten thousand dollars ($10,000).
344 Section 3. This act shall become effective on July 1,
345 2026.
